LinearEquation class

Instance Variables:
    private int x1 - This variable represents the x value of the first coordinate pair
    private int y1 - this variable represents the y value of the first coordinate pair
    private int x2 - this variable represents the x value of the second coordinate pair
    private int y2 - this variable represents the y value of the second coordinate pair
    private String m - this variable represents the slope of the 2 points
    private double yInt - this variable represents the y intercept of the 2 points
    private String slopeIntForm - this variable represents the slope intercept form of the 2 coordinates points
    private double distance - this variable represents the distance between the 2 points
    private double solvedY - this variable represents the y coordinate for the x value they input at the end
Constructor
	public LinearEquation(int x1, int y1, int x2, int y2)
    initializes each variable into the input inputted into the constructor

    public LinearEquation()
    empty object creator
Methods

    public void x1y1 (String input)
    this method substrings the coordinate typed and stores the values into the variables

	public void x2y2 (String input){
    this method substrings the coordinate typed and stores the values into the variables

	public void distanceAndSlope()
    calculates the distance and slope

	public void yIntercept()
    calculates the y intercept

	public void slopeInterceptForm()
    formats the variables into slope intercept form

	public int x1()
    returns value of x1

	public int y1()
    returns value of y1

    public int x2()
    returns value of x2

    public int y2()
    returns value of y2

    public void solver (double input)
    solves for the y coordinate given the x coordinate inputted into the parameter

    public String toString()
    Step 1: This method will display all relevant information about this instance including:
            X and Y coordinate information of first pair and second pair
            Slope Intercept Form equation
            The Slope
            Distance between 2 points
EquationRunner.java
Step 1: Create a new object
Step 2: Ask user to enter first coordinate point
Step 3: use the x1y1 method
Step 4: Ask user to enter second coordinate point
Step 5: use the x2y2 method
Step 6: create new object class with the constructor with parameters
Step 7: Print out the result using toString method
Step 8: Ask the user to enter third coordinate point
Step 9: Use the solver method and input the user's input into the parameter
